title: Zombie
lyrics:
Zombie, oh, zombie
Zombie no go go unless you tell am to go
Zombie no go stop unless you tell am to stop
Zombie no go turn unless you tell am to turn
Zombie no go think unless you tell am to think

title: Raga Khamaj
lyrics: A highly improvisational piece for sitar and tabla. It begins with a slow, meditative 'alap' section, exploring the melodic contours of the raga, before progressing to a rhythmic 'gat' with intricate interplay between the instruments.

chord_progression.tonality: Based on the Khamaj thaat (equivalent to Mixolydian mode), with a drone on Sa (C) and Pa (G).

title: Ai Du
artist: Ali Farka Touré ft. Ry Cooder
lyrics: Features Touré's signature hypnotic, cyclical guitar style and vocals in Songhai. The song has a laid-back, bluesy feel with sparse, resonant instrumentation that evokes the Malian landscape.

title: Mundian To Bach Ke
lyrics:
Mundian to bach ke rahi
Ni billo, mundian to bach ke rahi
(Beware of the boys, oh girl, beware of the boys)
A fusion of Bhangra vocals and rhythm with the bassline from the 'Knight Rider' theme song.

title: Didi
lyrics:
Didi, didi, didi wah
Ouah didi, didi, bghitha, bghitha ou ma andi zouj
(Didi, oh didi, I want her, I want her and I don't have a penny)
A global hit blending traditional Algerian Raï with pop and funk elements.

title: Water No Get Enemy
lyrics:
If you want to quench your thirst, you drink water
If your head dey hot, you use water
Water, him no get enemy
Water, him no get enemy

title: Mustt Mustt (Lost in His Work)
lyrics:
Dam mast qalandar, mast, mast
Ik vird hai dam dam Ali Ali
(A joyous trance, ecstatic, ecstatic
Every breath is a prayer to Ali)
A devotional Sufi song with powerful, improvisational vocals and driving tabla rhythms.

title: 7 Seconds
lyrics:
And when a child is born into this world
It has no concept of the tone the skin is living in
And it's not a second
7 seconds away
Just as long as I stay, I'll be waiting

title: Bamboléo
lyrics:
Bamboléo, bamboléa
Porque mi vida, yo la prefiero vivir así
Bamboléo, bamboléa
Porque mi vida, yo la prefiero vivir así

title: Pata Pata
lyrics:
Pata Pata is the name of a dance
We do down Johannesburg way
And everybody starts to move
As soon as Pata Pata starts to play

title: O-Daiko
lyrics: A powerful and visceral performance centered on the 'O-daiko' (large drum). Features thunderous, driving rhythms, dynamic shifts, and highly choreographed, athletic drumming.

chord_progression.description: Primarily rhythmic; non-pitched percussion. Harmony is not a structural element.

title: Chant to the Mother
lyrics: An atmospheric piece featuring Tuvan throat singing techniques (khoomei, sygyt, kargyraa). The singers produce multiple pitches simultaneously, creating an otherworldly drone and overtone melody accompanied by traditional instruments.

chord_progression.description: Based on a pedal drone (D) with vocal overtones creating shifting harmonic textures.

title: Homeless
lyrics:
Homeless, homeless, moonlight sleeping on a midnight lake
Homeless, homeless, moonlight sleeping on a midnight lake
We are homeless, we are homeless, the moonlight sleeping on a midnight lake

title: Agolo
lyrics:
Agolo, agolo, agolo, eh
Agolo, agolo, agolo, ah
(Lyrics are in Yoruba, celebrating life and movement)
A high-energy fusion of traditional Beninese rhythms with funk and pop.

title: Clandestino
lyrics:
Solo voy con mi pena
Sola va mi condena
Correr es mi destino
Para burlar la ley
Perdido en el corazón
De la grande Babylon
Me dicen el clandestino
Por no llevar papel

title: Tamacun
lyrics: An instrumental piece for two acoustic guitars, blending fast flamenco strumming, percussive techniques, and heavy metal-influenced riffs. It's energetic, virtuosic, and highly rhythmic.

title: Yamay
lyrics:
Yamay, yamay, yamay-o
(Lyrics in Mandinka, a call and response celebrating community)
A groove-based Afropop track with soaring vocals, intricate guitar work, and layered percussion.

title: Samba de Verão
lyrics:
Você viu só que amor, nunca vi coisa assim
E eu passei, 'tava de bobeira, nem te vi
Você passou, perto de mim, sem me ver
E eu, sem graça, quebrei a cara

title: Ja Funmi
lyrics:
(Ja Funmi means 'Fight For Me' in Yoruba)
An intricate and polyrhythmic Jùjú track featuring interlocking guitar melodies, talking drums, and call-and-response vocals.

title: Djarabi
lyrics: An instrumental piece performed on the kora, a West African harp. The music is characterized by its cascading, layered melodies, creating a complex and beautiful texture that is both rhythmic and serene.

title: Afro-Rock
lyrics: A high-energy instrumental fusion of Ghanaian highlife, funk, rock, and jazz. Features a prominent horn section, driving percussion, and psychedelic organ solos.

title: Cler Achel
lyrics:
(Lyrics in Tamashek about the Tuareg struggle and identity)
A hypnotic desert blues track built on a cyclical electric guitar riff, handclaps, and call-and-response vocals.

title: Aquarela do Brasil
lyrics:
Brasil, meu Brasil brasileiro
Meu mulato inzoneiro
Vou cantar-te nos meus versos
O Brasil, samba que dá
Bamboleio, que faz gingar
O Brasil do meu amor
Terra de Nosso Senhor

title: Rhythms of the Ganges
lyrics: An instrumental piece that fuses the melodic structures of Indian classical music, played on sitar, with modern electronic beats, basslines, and tabla rhythms.

chord_progression.tonality: Based on an Indian raga with a drone, blended with electronic basslines implying minor-key harmony (Dm).

title: Jarabi
lyrics:
(Jarabi means 'Passion' in Bambara)
A modern take on Wassoulou music from Mali, featuring Sangaré's powerful voice over a blend of traditional instruments like the kamalengoni (youth harp) and modern bass and guitar.
